The paper focuses on improving the generalization of deep learning models through automated data augmentation, specifically in the context of image classification and object detection. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning models and optimization techniques, which are common topics in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) datasets, which suggests a possible connection to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of hyperparameters to investigate the role of data augmentation, which suggests a possible connection to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
